# Product Requirement Document (PRD): LLM Crawlability Audit

## 1. System Overview & Architecture
The **LLM Crawlability Audit** is an on-demand, standalone feature allowing users to evaluate how easily AI search engines, RAG pipelines, and agentic web scrapers can discover, parse, and trust a project's web pages. 

### 1.1 Architectural Boundaries
* **Isolation:** This feature operates **completely independently** of the main 18-step workflow pipeline. It reads/writes to its own database tables and must not block or depend on `server/src/features/workflow`.
* **Execution:** Triggered exclusively on-demand via the frontend dashboard or fetched by the on-demand agent context-builder pipeline.

