## 3. Database & Data Model Specification

### 3.1 Schema Definition (`llm_audit_results`)
Implement using Drizzle ORM syntax mapping exactly to these column profiles:

| Column Name | Data Type | Modifiers / Constraints | Description |
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
| `id` | `uuid` | Primary Key | Unique identifier for each audited page row. |
| `project_id` | `uuid` | Foreign Key → `projects.id` (ON DELETE CASCADE) | Ties the audit results to a specific user project. |
| `audit_run_id` | `uuid` | Not Null | A shared UUID grouping all pages analyzed during a single batch run. |
| `page_url` | `text` | Not Null | The full, absolute target URL audited. |
| `ai_indexability_score`| `integer`| Not Null | Composite score bounded between `0` and `100`. |
| `bot_permissions` | `jsonb` | Not Null | Structured map of monitored bots (Allowed/Blocked/Not Specified). |
| `content_checks` | `jsonb` | Not Null | Flags for HTML structure, semantic usage, and Single Page App detection. |
| `trust_signals` | `jsonb` | Not Null | Security, metadata, and schema markup checks. |
| `content_chunking` | `jsonb` | Not Null | Readability and formatting structure markers. |
| `issues` | `jsonb` | Not Null | Array of objects representing active warnings/errors with fix instructions. |
| `audited_at` | `timestamp`| Default `now()`, Indexed | Exact timestamp of execution. |

### 3.2 Required Query Indexing
Ensure the migration includes the following index structures for retrieval performance:
* `(project_id)` — Project lookup optimization.
* `(audit_run_id)` — Run lookup optimization.
* `(project_id, audit_run_id)` — Fetch latest run for a project optimized query.

