## 6. Issue & Remediation Mapping Matrix
When executing audits, generate structural issue warnings utilizing this exact categorization matrix:

| Type | Severity | Trigger | Frontend UI `fix` Instruction String |
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
| `bot_blocked` | High | An LLM bot is blocked in `robots.txt`. | Update your robots.txt to allow access for this specific AI agent user-agent. |
| `schema` | High | No JSON-LD found on the page. | Embed a structured JSON-LD data schema block on this page. |
| `schema` | Medium | Schema present but no AI-priority types (`Article`, `FAQPage`, `HowTo`). | Expand your JSON-LD schema to include AI-preferred semantic entities like Article or FAQPage. |
| `sitemap` | High | No valid `sitemap.xml` at `/sitemap.xml`. | Generate and publish a valid sitemap.xml file inside your website's root directory. |
| `sitemap` | Medium | Page URL not found in the sitemap. | Ensure this page URL is properly indexed inside your primary sitemap.xml. |
| `structure` | Varies | Content structure check failures. | Fix structural HTML issues, rectify heading hierarchies, or add missing alt strings. |
| `trust` | Varies | Missing trust signal indicators. | Ensure the page is served over secure HTTPS protocols and features transparent author attributes. |
| `chunking` | Varies | Poor paragraph length or link count. | Format dense copy walls into short paragraph blocks (2-4 sentences) and add clear lists. |

